-- LDP's Tanigaki Says He'll Resign If Ruling DPJ Wins Upper House Majority
-- Kana Nishizawa
-- 2010-06-13T05:36:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-13/ldp-s-tanigaki-says-he-ll-resign-if-ruling-dpj-wins-upper-house-majority.html

          
          
             Sadakazu Tanigaki, president of
Japan’s opposition Liberal Democratic Party, said he will resign
if the ruling Democratic Party of Japan wins a majority in upper
house elections next month. Tanigaki spoke on Fuji Television
Network Inc.’s Shin-Hodo 2001 program broadcast today.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Kana Nishizawa in Tokyo at 
 knishizawa5@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        